Step-by-Step Execution in Exam
✅ STEP 1 — Create New Project

Open Android Studio → New Project
Select Empty Activity
Name: RecyclerViewDemo
Package: com.example.recyclerviewdemo
Language: Java
Min SDK: API 21
Click Finish → Wait for Gradle


✅ STEP 2 — Add RecyclerView Dependency in build.gradle

In left panel: Gradle Scripts → build.gradle (Module: app)
Inside dependencies { } block, add:

gradleimplementation 'androidx.recyclerview:recyclerview:1.3.0'

Click "Sync Now" (yellow bar at top)
⚠️ Wait for sync to complete before next step


✅ STEP 3 — Edit activity_main.xml

Go to: res → layout → activity_main.xml
Click Code tab → Replace everything with XML below


✅ STEP 4 — Create item_view.xml (Layout for Each List Item)

Right-click res/layout → New → Layout Resource File
Name: item_view
Root element: LinearLayout
Click OK → Paste item XML code below


✅ STEP 5 — Create MyAdapter.java

Right-click java → com.example.recyclerviewdemo
